  "instructions": [
    "Thaw the frozen seafood by running it under cold water for 5 minutes and pat dry.",
    "Heat 1 tbsp of vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium\u2011high heat.",
    "Add the seafood to the skillet and cook for 3\u20134 minutes until it turns opaque and slightly golden.",
    "Stir in sesame oil, sriracha, soy sauce, rice vinegar, and honey; cook for an additional minute so the sauce coats the seafood.",
    "While the seafood cooks, warm 1 cup of jasmine rice according to package instructions.",
    "Dice cucumber and mix it with pickled ginger and chopped scallions in a serving bowl.",
    "Transfer the cooked rice to the bowl, top with the seared seafood and its sauce, then sprinkle toasted sesame seeds.",
    "Serve immediately, allowing the crisp flavor of the seafood to mingle with the fresh cucumber and spicy sauce."
  ],
